!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = patientid: patient1
!Sample_growth_protocol_ch1 = For single cell suspension kidneys were dissected and incubated for 40 min at 37Â°C in RPMI medium (including 0.01 M HEPES; 0.5 mL filtered FBS and 0.4Âµg/ mL DNase and 8 Âµg/ mL collagenase D). The samples were homogenized using a gentleMACS (Miltenyi Biotec).
!Sample_molecule_ch1 = total RNA
!Sample_extract_protocol_ch1 = Cells were loaded on a 10x Chromium single cell instrument.
!Sample_extract_protocol_ch1 = All steps were performed according to standard protocol of the Chromium single cell 5â v2 kit to generate high-quality cDNA libraries.
!Sample_description = 10x Genomics
!Sample_description = Patient1_GEX
!Sample_data_processing = 10x Genomics raw sequencing data were processed using CellRanger software (version 5.0.0, 10x Genomics, Pleasanton, CA) and the human genome GRCh38-2020-A release as the reference (function cellranger count). The matrices of cells and the unique molecular identifier (UMI) count were obtained and further processed by the R package Seurat (version 4.0.1)
!Sample_data_processing = To remove potential doublets, cutoff values for number of expressed genes (nGene) were determined for samples following visual inspection of the distribution of nGene and nUMI for each cell. The cells with higher nGene values were excluded. We further removed low-quality cells with high mitochondrial genes of all detected genes
!Sample_data_processing = Assembly: GRCh38-2020-A
!Sample_data_processing = Supplementary files format and content: Tab-separated values files and matrix files
